The Corpus of REcommendation STrength is a collection of HTML-formatted
clinical guidelines annotated with the location of recommendations.
Recommendations are labelled with an author-provided indicator of their
strength of importance. As data is drawn from many disparate authors, a unified
scheme of importance labels is defined, together with a mapping for each
guideline.

Please see the original paper for a detailed description of the corpus:

